programme.desc: Water quality is everything—and the Star brite - SeaSafe team is back at it for the second year in a row! Led by Cory Redwine, Conservation Director of Project SeaSafe, this is the 4th Annual Clean Water Collective and it’s bigger than ever. This time, we’re in Grant, Florida, where 4 million clams are being released into the Indian River Lagoon, paired with the planting of thousands of mangroves, oyster work by CCA and trash clean ups to help restore one of Florida’s most critical ecosystems. But it’s not just about hard work—it’s about connection. With local captains, fishing legends, and the Local Knowledge crew on hand, we hit the water to show why this place is worth fighting for. From clam drops by drone, to in-water mangrove planting, to monster snook catches, this is hands-on conservation at its best. This two-part series kicks off with action, heart, and the kind of hope only a healthy waterway can bring. Don’t miss Part 1—where conservation meets community and everyone gets their hands wet.

The bite wasn't easy, but that didn't stop Rush from smashing his personal best - not once, but twice - in one unforgettable day on the water. programme.desc: On this episode of Midwest Whitetail, we follow along with Mike Reed as he closes the chapter on yet another River Farm legend. Fast forward all these years later and Mike's plan to hunt the ghostly buck finally came to fruition. Join Mike as he dives into his step by step process for hunting "DK" during the 2023 season dating back to finding the shed antler after a controlled burn in the spring. This one has it all from bucks chasing, buck vocalizations, 10 yard shots, and another recovery that saw Mike take to the river! Let us know in the comments what questions you have and as always, thank you so much for taking the time to watch another episode of Midwest Whitetail.

programme.title: Four Bucks In Three Days, Key Locations To Hunt During The Lockdown Phase
programme.desc: On this week's show we catch up with Owen Reigler in Southern Iowa who shares a few tips and strategies as gun seasons enter the fold across the country. Next, we head to Southern Illinois with Chad Holmes for a bow hunt on the day before the state's opening day of gun season. Experiencing the full force of the peak rut, Chad no sooner climbs out of his stand for the morning than hears a chase headed straight for him. The following day, his son Casen Holmes heads to a Redneck blind hoping to cash in on opening day of the Illinois firearms season. After that, we catch up with David Williams and Andy Melton who also gear up for the gun opener in Illinois. Hoping to key in on historical hot spots during the lockdown phase on their farms, the guys find themselves with back to back opportunities to fill their gun tags on two mature bucks. Looking forward, the team still has some awesome stories to share with you so be sure to stay tuned in as we move through the month of December. Thank you as always for your support!

A roller coaster filled with the lowest of lows to the highest of highs, we couldn't be more excited to share this one with you. Kaleb Greiner entered the 2023 hunting season with high hopes but he could have never predicted what followed next. Between stacking up a hitlist that included 3 bucks over 175", an EHD outbreak that decimates the deer heard, and a face to face 10 yard bow shot with a 177" giant, this is the story of Kaleb's one in a million hunting season here in Iowa.
